definition.value: An N,N-disubstituted benzenesulfonamide bearing an unsubstituted amino group at the 4-position, used for the treatment of HIV infection. A second-generation HIV protease inhibitor, darunavir was designed to form robust interactions with the protease  enzyme from many strains of HIV, including those from treatment-experienced patients with multiple resistance mutations to other protease inhibitors.
A  chlorobiphenyl carrying a single chloro substituent at unspecified position.
Any polychlorobiphenyl with molecular formula C12H8Cl2.
Any polychlorobiphenyl with molecular formula C12H7Cl3.
Any polychlorobiphenyl with molecular formula C12H6Cl4.
Any polychlorobiphenyl with molecular formula C12H5Cl5.
Any polychlorobiphenyl with molecular formula C12H4Cl6.
A C21-steroid that is pregnane which contains a double bond between positions 4 and 5 and is substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and by hydroxy groups at the 17alpha and 20 positions.
Any alkyldiacylglyceride in which the alkyl group is located at position 1 and the acyl groups at positions 2 and 3.
A C21-steroid that is pregnane which contains a double bond between positions 4 and 5 and is substituted by an oxo group at position 3 and a hydroxy group at position 20.
A C21-steroid that is pregnenolone in which a hydrogen attached to a carbon is substituted by a hydroxy group.
Compounds based on a biladiene skeleton.
A pinene that is bicyclo[3.1.1]hept-2-ene substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6 and 6 respectively.
A p-menthane monoterpenoid that is p-menthane substituted by an oxo group at position 3.
A bilin that consists of 3,18-diethyl-2,7,13,17-tetramethyl-1,19,22,24-tetrahydro-21H-biline-8,12-dipropanoic acid bearing two oxo substituents at positions 1 and 19.
Compounds containing two pyrrole rings linked through a methine group (-CH=).
A 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylic acid in which the chiral centre has R configuration.
A pyrrolecarboxylic acid that is 1H-pyrrole carrying a carboxy substituent at position 2.
Any sesquiterpenoid whose structure is related to eremophilane.
A sesquiterpene that is dodecane substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6 and 10.
A diterpenoid compound having an ent-kaurane skeleton.
The product resulting from formal oxidation of DL-proline by loss of hydrogen from the nitrogen and from the carbon alpha to the carboxylic acid, with the formation of a C=N bond.
A diterpenoid based on an  abietane skeleton.
